      <hedline>
        <hl1>RYE: TEACHER HONORED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Peter Beller</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Beller, Peter</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Laura Klein, fourth-grade teacher at Osborn Elementary School in Rye, NY, wins 1999 Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching; she plans to use $7,500 grant to start family math night program (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Laura Klein, a fourth-grade teacher at Osborn Elementary School in Rye has won the 1999 Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching, the government's highest honor for elementary and high school teachers. Ms. Klein, who has been teaching for 13 years, three of them at Osborn, will receive a $7,500 grant for her school, which she plans to use, in part, to start a ''family math night'' program.</p>
        <p>Peter Beller</p>
      </block>
